displayName: Pirate Ship of the Great Merchant Acreo

parameters: Cors the Wanderer: Alright, with this, it's all connected.
Cors the Wanderer: Ahaha, is everyone alright?

Guild Leader Agonia: Drag Acreo, who is inside the ship, out
onto the deck.

Guild Leader Agonia: It's highly likely that the enemy is
armed, so it's best to assume that they have allies as well.
Guild Leader Agonia: Alright, I'll be waiting here.

Cors the Wanderer: ...Are you alright? Being the one in
charge is tough, huh?

Guild Leader Agonia: I've always been bad with ships...
*burp*

Cors the Wanderer: Ahaha, knowing the weakness of the guild
leader who can silence even crying children is worth
something.

Guild Leader Agonia: Please keep it a secret. It's for both
of our sakes.
Guild Leader Agonia: Good work, Clea.

Great Merchant Acreo: Ugh... spare me. It's true that I
tried to deceive my younger brother, I admit that...

Great Merchant Acreo: But, I shouldn't have caused any
trouble for you guys. If it's money, I'll pay. I'll pay back
ten times, no, a hundred times the original amount!

Guild Leader Agonia: Do you remember what you did to your
younger brother? You betrayed his trust.

Great Merchant Acreo: C-Clea! I'll pay you a reward that's a
hundred times the original amount, so please!

Cors the Wanderer: Excuse me, Acreo-san. You were secretly
doing business in the sea without our knowledge, right?

Cors the Wanderer: The organization no longer has any reason
to show you any kindness.

Great Merchant Acreo: P-Please... forgive me. I promise I
will be of use to the guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: Clea, this is the last lesson for
today. There is only one role for those who break the three
principles of the guild.
Great Merchant Acreo: Ahh, my hand, my hand!!

Guild Leader Agonia: The death of the Great Merchant Acreo,
who serves as a tool to demonstrate the consequences of
betrayal to both internal and external parties, will become
a significant deterrent.

Guild Leader Agonia: Mercy is unnecessary. Anyone who breaks
the three principles is subject to complete elimination.
Clea: ...I will keep it in mind.

Guild Leader Agonia: There won't be any reward, but I
suppose there's no helping it. Shall we sink the ship and
then return?
